<HEADLINE>
UNIVERSITIES TO HOLD HOLIDAY ACTIVITIES FOR FOREIGN STUDENTS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Feb. 16 (CNA) 02/16/07  15:04:01 (By Steve Bercic)
</P>
<P>
Several Taiwan universities have planned a series of Lunar New
Year activities for foreign students to give them the opportunity
to enjoy a traditional Taiwan holiday celebration experience
first-hand, according to the Ministry of Education's (MOE's)
Bureau of International Cultural &amp; Educational Relations.
</P>
<P>
According to MOE tallies, there are currently more than 13,000
foreign students pursuing degrees or enrolled in Chinese-language
learning programs at universities around Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
To give these foreign students a taste of local culture during
the festive season, more than ten universities have arranged
various holiday activities, including couplet writing, lantern
design, and reunion dinner events, officials at the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
Among the universities arranging holiday activities for foreign
students are National Chi Nan University in Puli, Nantou County,
and National Taiwan Ocean University in Keelung City, which will
each hold a special dinner party on the night before Chinese New
Year's Eve. Meanwhile, Kai Nan University in Luchu, Taoyuan
County has arranged for foreign students at the school to visit
the homes of Taiwan students to enjoy a traditional reunion
dinner on Lunar New Year's Eve with a real Taiwanese family.
</P>
<P>
Several universities have also planned activities for the Lantern
Festival, which falls on the 15th day of the first month on the
lunar calendar and marks the end of the series of Chinese New
Year celebrations.
</P>
